# Frontend Agent Notes

This is an Angular 21 frontend, not a React runtime. A React/Vite reference UI exists under `Grievance Management System UI`; use it only as visual/product reference when improving Angular screens.

## Architecture

- App shell: `src/app/app.component.*`
- Routes: `src/app/app.routes.ts`
- Role session service: `src/app/core/auth/role-session.service.ts`
- Login / role entry: `src/app/features/login`
- Citizen status lookup: `src/app/features/citizen`
- Caller desk: `src/app/features/caller`
- Management dashboard: `src/app/features/management`
- Super Admin access UI: `src/app/features/super-admin`
- Dashboard: `src/app/features/dashboard`
- Complaint components and API code: `src/app/features/complaints`
- Shared UI primitives: `src/app/shared/components`
- Styling: Tailwind CSS in `src/styles.css` and `tailwind.config.js`

## Backend Integration

The frontend talks to the local NestJS backend at `http://localhost:3000`.

Primary endpoints:

- `GET /complaints`
- `GET /complaints/:id`
- `POST /complaints`
- `PATCH /complaints/:id`
- `DELETE /complaints/:id`

The Angular service is `src/app/features/complaints/data/complaints.service.ts`. Keep frontend types in `complaint.model.ts` aligned with backend DTOs and entities.

Current backend complaint DTO fields are `citizen`, `mobile`, `department`, `subject`, `ward`, `source`, `priority`, optional `status`, and optional `assignedTo`. Do not send non-whitelisted fields because the NestJS backend uses strict validation. The read model also tolerates legacy records containing `citizenName`, `phone`, or `description`.

## Role Workspaces

- `/login`: Select Citizen, Caller, Management, or Super Admin.
- `/citizen`: Ticket status lookup using `GET /complaints/:id`.
- `/caller`: Shows today's IVR complaints and ticket creation counts from complaint data.
- `/management`: Shows overall ticket metrics and caller performance.
- `/super-admin`: Frontend-local access management UI until backend auth/access APIs are added.
- `/admin/dashboard`: Existing complaint operations dashboard.

## Working Rules

- Use standalone Angular components and typed inputs/outputs.
- Prefer reactive forms for forms that submit to the backend.
- Keep Tailwind utility styling consistent with the existing government dashboard UI.
- Do not edit files inside `Grievance Management System UI` unless intentionally updating the React reference.
- Run `npm run build` before handing off frontend changes.
- If the UI appears unchanged, check for stale Angular dev servers on both `4200` and `4201`.
